### [Job Chapter 25](../../../bib/kjv/job025.htm#001.md)

[Job 25:2](../../../bib/kjv/job025.htm#002.md)

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_002">job 25:2</span></span>

BILDAD'S REPLY. ([Job 25:1-6](../../../bib/kjv/job025.htm#001).md)

Power and terror, that is, terror-inspiring power.

peace in his high places--implying that His power is such on high as to
quell all opposition, not merely there, but on earth also. The Holy
Ghost here shadowed forth Gospel truths ([Col
1:20](../../../bib/kjv/col001.htm#020.md); [Eph
1:10](../../../bib/kjv/eph001.htm#010).md).

