[Job 25:5](../../../bib/kjv/job025.htm#005.md)

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_005">job 25:5</span></span>

"Look up even unto the moon" ([Job
15:15](../../../bib/kjv/job015.htm#015).md). "Stars" here answer to
"saints" (angels) there; "the moon" here to "the heavens" there. Even
the "stars," the most dazzling object to man's eye, and the angels, of
which the stars are emblems ([Job
4:18](../../../bib/kjv/job004.htm#018.md); [Rev
9:1](../../../bib/kjv/rev009.htm#001).md), are imperfect in His sight.
Theirs is the light and purity but of creatures; His of the Creator.

[Job 25:6](../../../bib/kjv/job025.htm#006.md)

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_006">job 25:6</span></span>

([Job 4:19-21](../../../bib/kjv/job004.htm#019.md); [Job
15:16](../../../bib/kjv/job015.htm#016).md).

worm . . . worm--Two distinct Hebrew words. The first, a worm bred in
putridity; alluding to man's corruption. The second a crawling worm;
implying that man is weak and grovelling.

